German[edit]

Etymology[edit]

From Old High German odar. Related to Old English oþþe.

Pronunciation[edit]

  • IPA(key): /ˈʔoːdɐ/
  • audio
    		(file)

Conjunction[edit]

oder

  1. or
    Danach alles gestr. oder noch 1–2 Wörter?
    Is everything after that crossed out or are there one or two more words?

Particle[edit]

oder

  1. (tag question) right?; is it?; is it not?
    Es ist kalt heute, oder? ― It’s cold today, isn’t it?
    Das war keine so gute Idee, oder? ― That wasn’t such a good idea, was it?
    Du kommst aus Deutschland, oder? ― You come from Germany, don’t you?

Synonyms[edit]

  • (tag question): gell, ne, nicht, nicht wahr, wa

See also[edit]

  • alles oder nichts
